<p>I have an AngularJS project where I open a modal window. In the modalwindow I have an iframe wich loads a external URL. The external url has a form. </p>  <p>Is there a way to access the formvalues without using jquery?</p>  <hr>  <p>So I've got a modal called from my controller:</p>  <pre><code>    var modalInstance = $modal.open({         templateUrl : 'modal.html',         controller  : 'ModalController',         size        : "lg",         resolve: {           options: function () {             return {               iframeUrl         : â€œhttp://www.myexternalurl",             };           }         }                 }); </code></pre>  <p>modal.html</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="modal-dialog"&gt;     &lt;iframe ng-src="{{options.iframeUrl}}" id="myIframe" sandbox="allow-same-origin allow-scripts" class="modalIframe"  seamless='seamless' style="border:0" frameBorder="0"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Modal controller</p>  <pre><code>.controller('ModalController' , ['$scope', '$modalInstance' , '$sce' , 'options' , '$document'  , function($scope, $modalInstance , $sce , options , $document) {          $scope.options  = null;      if(options) {         $scope.options  = options;          if($scope.options.iframeUrl) {              $scope.options.iframeUrl = $sce.trustAsResourceUrl($scope.options.iframeUrl);              $modalInstance.rendered.then(function(){               var myElement = angular.element($document[0].querySelector('#myIframe'));               console.log(myElement);               console.log(myElement.find("form"));             });                     }     } }]); </code></pre>  <p>Form on the external url</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form id="myForm"&gt; &lt;input type='text' name='test'&gt; &lt;/form&gt; </code></pre>  <p>So from the modal controller I need to access the form (loaded in the iframe) and get the values from the input named test</p>